inconsistencies in her story,

26:24.383 --> 26:27.319 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the woman said she made the
whole thing up. Except, there's

26:27.352 --> 26:31.423 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
more, "An Unbelievable Story of
Rape" is the joint effort by two

26:31.457 --> 26:34.393 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
non-profit news organizations,
The Marshall Project and

26:34.426 --> 26:37.863 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ProPublica, to tell the tale of
how two very different police

26:37.896 --> 26:41.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
departments treated the
investigation. We are joined now

26:41.166 --> 26:44.470 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
by co-author Ken Armstrong, a
staff writer for The Marshall

26:44.503 --> 26:48.307 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Project. He joins from Seattle.
So, Ken, I want to ask, I want

26:48.340 --> 26:51.343 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to tell our audience that we are
going to talk about the ends of

26:51.376 --> 26:54.613 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this story as well f they hadn't
read it yet. But what happens to

26:54.646 --> 26:57.149 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this woman when she goes into a
police department in Linwood,

26:57.182 --> 26:59.852 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Washington, and tells them this
she has been raped? KEN

26:59.885 --> 27:03.222 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ARMSTRONG, THE MARSHALL PROJECT:
Well, she tells police that she

27:03.255 --> 27:06.892 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
