detectives decide to confront

27:41.293 --> 27:45.264 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the victim in this case, to
confront Marie, about whether

27:45.297 --> 27:48.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
she, what she has reported has
really happened. So, they bring

27:48.433 --> 27:51.637 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
her into the police station. And
they interrogate her as a

27:51.670 --> 27:55.774 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
criminal suspect, instead of
questioning her as a rape

27:55.807 --> 28:00.412 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
victim. And you know, she was 18
years old. She had no experience

28:00.445 --> 28:04.283 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with police. In the face of this
interrogation, she took what

28:04.316 --> 28:07.185 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
under the circumstances she
considered to be the easiest way

28:07.219 --> 28:12.024 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
out, which was to say, "I lied
about what had happened." So

28:12.057 --> 28:15.661 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
