30:54.386 --> 30:57.456 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
fraction, but it's an unknown
number. SREENIVASAN: So, why did

30:57.489 --> 31:01.793 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Colorado department behave
so differently when they were

31:01.827 --> 31:05.564 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
tracking their suspect based on
interviews that they had with

31:05.597 --> 31:10.435 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
victims, versus the Washington
department? ARMSTRONG: You know,

31:10.469 --> 31:16.274 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the story proved to be a
remarkable contrast in the dos

31:16.308 --> 31:19.878 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and don'ts of investigating
rape. Everything that the police

31:19.911 --> 31:24.049 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Washington did wrong, the
police in Colorado did right.

31:24.082 --> 31:28.186 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They listened to their victims.
They pursue the evidence,

31:28.220 --> 31:31.857 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
